{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T09:05:19.369Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In hierarchical agent architectures and distributed multi-agent swarms, "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"inter-agent communication protocols"},{"type":"text","text":" are the technical mechanisms that let agents exchange structured messages across machines or services. The two dominant families are "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"gRPC"},{"type":"text","text":" for fast, typed, synchronous or streaming calls and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"message queues"},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g., Kafka, RabbitMQ, Redis) for decoupled, resilient, and asynchronous workflows. The choice between them determines whether your swarm is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"tight-coupled and real-time"},{"type":"text","text":" (gRPC) or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"loose-coupled and fault-tolerant"},{"type":"text","text":" (queues)."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What it is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"gRPC"},{"type":"text","text":" is a high-performance RPC framework that:\n- Uses "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"HTTP/2"},{"type":"text","text":" as the transport.\n- Exposes "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"strictly typed service definitions"},{"type":"text","text":" (via "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".proto"},{"type":"text","text":" files).\n- Supports "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"binary serialization"},{"type":"text","text":" (Protobuf) for efficiency.\n- Enables "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"streaming RPCs"},{"type":"text","text":" (client, server, or bidirectional).\n- Is ideal for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"internal enterprise"},{"type":"text","text":" communication between agents that need low latency and type safety."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Message queues"},{"type":"text","text":" are broker-based systems that:\n- Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"publish-subscribe"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"task queue"},{"type":"text","text":" patterns.\n- Provide "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"durable queues"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"retries"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"dead-letter"},{"type":"text","text":" handling.\n- Decouple producers (agents sending tasks) from consumers (agents executing tasks).\n- Are ideal for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"asynchronous, resilient workflows"},{"type":"text","text":" where agents don’t need to be online simultaneously."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why it matters"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In a distributed swarm or hierarchical architecture, agents must:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Coordinate"},{"type":"text","text":": Orchestrator delegates subtasks to specialists.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Exchange state"},{"type":"text","text":": Share intermediate results, checkpoints, and context.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Handle failures"},{"type":"text","text":": Retries, timeouts, and error propagation.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Scale"},{"type":"text","text":": Support many agents working in parallel."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The communication protocol determines:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Latency"},{"type":"text","text":": gRPC is faster (binary, HTTP/2) than queues (text, broker overhead).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Fault tolerance"},{"type":"text","text":": Queues provide durable storage and automatic retries; gRPC requires custom retry logic.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Coupling"},{"type":"text","text":": gRPC is synchronous (caller waits for response); queues are asynchronous (caller sends and continues).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Complexity"},{"type":"text","text":": gRPC requires "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".proto"},{"type":"text","text":" definitions and stubs; queues require broker setup and messageFormats."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mental model"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of gRPC as a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"phone call"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- You call an agent’s endpoint.\n- You wait for the response.\n- The connection is live and fast.\n- If the agent is down, the call fails immediately."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of message queues as a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"postal service"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- You drop a message in a mailbox (queue).\n- The agent picks it up later.\n- The message is stored durably.\n- If the agent is down, the message waits."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How it works"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"gRPC pattern"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In gRPC, you define services in "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".proto"},{"type":"text","text":" files:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"proto"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"// agent.proto\nservice AgentService {\n  rpc ExecuteTask(TaskRequest) returns (TaskResponse);\n  rpc StreamProgress(TaskRequest) returns (stream ProgressUpdate);\n}\n\nmessage TaskRequest {\n  string task_id = 1;\n  string goal = 2;\n}\n\nmessage TaskResponse {\n  string result = 1;\n  bool success = 2;\n}\n\nmessage ProgressUpdate {\n  string task_id = 1;\n  string status = 2;\n  int32 progress = 3;\n}"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Clients generate stubs and call RPCs:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# client.py\nimport agent_pb2_grpc\nimport agent_pb2\n\nstub = agent_pb2_grpc.AgentServiceStub(channel)\nrequest = agent_pb2.TaskRequest(task_id=\"123\", goal=\"scrape pricing\")\nresponse = stub.ExecuteTask(request)  # synchronous"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For streaming (e.g., progress updates):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"response_stream = stub.StreamProgress(request)  # server streaming\nfor update in response_stream:\n    print(f\"Progress: {update.progress}%\")"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key gRPC best practices:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Reuse stubs and channels"},{"type":"text","text":" to avoid connection overhead.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use keepalive pings"},{"type":"text","text":" to keep HTTP/2 connections alive.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use streaming RPCs"},{"type":"text","text":" for long-lived flows (e.g., task progress).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Favor callback API"},{"type":"text","text":" for high-QPS workloads."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Message queue pattern"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In a message queue (e.g., Celery + Redis, Kafka, RabbitMQ), agents publish tasks and workers consume them:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# producer.py (orchestrator)\nimport celery\n\ncelery_app = Celery(\"agent_swarm\", broker=\"redis://localhost:6379/0\")\n\n@celery_app.task\ndef run_subagent(domain: str, task: dict):\n    subagent = get_subagent_by_domain(domain)\n    return subagent.invoke(task)\n\n# Orchestrator dispatches tasks\nfor subtask in subtasks:\n    run_subagent.send(subtask[\"domain\"], subtask)  # enqueues to queue\n# consumer.py (worker)\n@celery_app.task(name=\"run_subagent\")\ndef run_subagent(domain: str, task: dict):\n    subagent = get_subagent_by_domain(domain)\n    return subagent.invoke(task)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key queue patterns:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Request-Response"},{"type":"text","text":": Agent sends task, waits for response (via reply queue).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Publish-Subscribe"},{"type":"text","text":": Agent broadcasts event, multiple subscribers receive it.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Task Queue"},{"type":"text","text":": Agent pushes task to queue, worker pulls and executes."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Communication patterns"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pattern"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"gRPC"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Message queues"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Request-Response"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Native (blocking RPC)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Via reply queue (async)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Publish-Subscribe"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Via server streaming"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Native (Kafka topics, RabbitMQ fanout)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Task Queue"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Not native (custom)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Native (Celery, RabbitMQ)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Streaming"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Native (HTTP/2 streams)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Via event streams (Kafka)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Durability"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Not durable (in-memory)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Durable (broker storage)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Retry"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Custom (client-side)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Built-in (broker-side)"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"When to use gRPC"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use gRPC when:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Low latency"},{"type":"text","text":" is critical (e.g., real-time coordination).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Type safety"},{"type":"text","text":" is required (e.g., strict schemas via "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".proto"},{"type":"text","text":").\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Streaming"},{"type":"text","text":" is needed (e.g., task progress, live updates).\n- Agents are "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"co-located"},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g., same VPC, same cluster).\n- You need "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"bidirectional communication"},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g., orchestrator ↔ subagent chat)."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"When to use message queues"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use message queues when:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Async workflows"},{"type":"text","text":" are required (e.g., queued tasks, delayed execution).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Fault tolerance"},{"type":"text","text":" is critical (e.g., durable retries, dead-letter).\n- Agents are "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"decoupled"},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g., different teams, different languages).\n- You need "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"scalability"},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g., many workers, many queues).\n- You need "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"pub-sub"},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g., broadcast events to multiple agents)."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Hybrid pattern"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Many systems use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"both"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"gRPC"},{"type":"text","text":" for real-time coordination (e.g., orchestrator → subagent RPC).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Message queues"},{"type":"text","text":" for async task dispatch (e.g., queued subtasks, batch jobs)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Orchestrator uses gRPC for coordination\nresponse = stub.ExecuteTask(request)  # synchronous\n\n# Orchestrator uses queues for async dispatch\nfor subtask in subtasks:\n    run_subagent.send(subtask[\"domain\"], subtask)  # async"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This gives you "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"fast coordination"},{"type":"text","text":" (gRPC) and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"resilient execution"},{"type":"text","text":" (queues)."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Trade-offs"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"gRPC benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Fast"},{"type":"text","text":": Binary serialization, HTTP/2.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Typed"},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".proto"},{"type":"text","text":" definitions enforce schemas.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Streaming"},{"type":"text","text":": Native support for live updates.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Synchronous"},{"type":"text","text":": Caller waits for response."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"gRPC trade-offs:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Not durable"},{"type":"text","text":": Messages are in-memory.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Requires stubs"},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".proto"},{"type":"text","text":" definitions and codegen.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Harder to debug"},{"type":"text","text":": Binary protocol."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Message queue benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Durable"},{"type":"text","text":": Messages stored in broker.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Resilient"},{"type":"text","text":": Automatic retries, dead-letter.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Async"},{"type":"text","text":": Caller doesn’t wait.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Decoupled"},{"type":"text","text":": Producers and consumers don’t know each other."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Message queue trade-offs:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Slower"},{"type":"text","text":": Broker overhead, text serialization.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Complex"},{"type":"text","text":": Requires broker setup and configuration.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Less typed"},{"type":"text","text":": No native schema enforcement (unless using additional tools)."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best practices"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use gRPC for internal, synchronous coordination"},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g., orchestrator ↔ subagent)."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use message queues for external, asynchronous workflows"},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g., queued tasks, batch execution)."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Reuse gRPC channels"},{"type":"text","text":" to avoid connection overhead."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use streaming RPCs"},{"type":"text","text":" for long-lived flows (e.g., progress updates)."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use durable queues"},{"type":"text","text":" for fault tolerance (e.g., retries, dead-letter)."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Define message formats"},{"type":"text","text":" clearly (e.g., JSON schema, "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".proto"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Pick one protocol"},{"type":"text","text":" and stick with it across all agents for consistency."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"gRPC"},{"type":"text","text":" is for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"fast, typed, synchronous/streaming"},{"type":"text","text":" coordination between co-located agents."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Message queues"},{"type":"text","text":" are for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"async, durable, fault-tolerant"},{"type":"text","text":" workflows with decoupled agents."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Many systems use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"both"},{"type":"text","text":": gRPC for real-time coordination, queues for async task dispatch."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"gRPC is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"low-latency"},{"type":"text","text":" but "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"not durable"},{"type":"text","text":"; queues are "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"durable"},{"type":"text","text":" but "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"slower"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The choice determines whether your swarm is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"tight-coupled"},{"type":"text","text":" (gRPC) or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"loose-coupled"},{"type":"text","text":" (queues)."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph"}]}}
